              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment was performed at RIKEN",
                "Accelerator Research Facility. Primary beam of 18-O",
                "was accelerated by cyclotron to 100 MeV/nucleon."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "KINDT"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "  The secondary beam of 15C was produced by",
                "fragmentation of 18-O on a 1.1 g/cm2 thick Be target.",
                "The secondary beam was separated using the RIPS",
                "fragment separator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "224 mg/cm2-thick Pb target located at the focal point",
                "of the fragment separator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN",
                "MWPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Used for incident beam characterization.",
                "Energy of incident 15C ion was determined by time of",
                "flight using pair of plastic scintillation detectors.",
                "Trajectory of 15C ions was determined by four sets of",
                "multiwire proportional counters."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons were detected by two layers of neutron",
                "hodoscope arrays with an effective area of",
                "2.14(W) x 0.92(H) m2 placed at 4.60 m and 4.99 m,",
                "respectively, downstream of the target. Each array",
                "consisted of 15 plastic scintillator rods with 6.1 cm",
                "thickness. The angular coverage ranged from -7.0deg to",
                "19.0deg in the horizontal direction, and from -5.5deg",
                "to 5.5deg in the vertical direction. The neutron",
                "momentum vector was determined from the time of flight",
                "and hit position information in the arrays."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP",
                "DRFTC",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 14C ions were analyzed by a magnetic",
                "spectrometer equipped with a drift chamber and plastic",
                "scintillator hodoscopes. Particle identification was",
                "performed by combining dE, time of flight data from",
                "the hodoscopes, and magnetic rigidity information from",
                "the tracking of the particle."
              ]
            }
          ],
